javadoc:
A best-effort cache of MD5 values of files, where the file is identified by its parent's
 MD5 combined with the file's path inside its parent's 'namespace'.

methods.name: add
methods.comment: Adds a filename mapping to this cache.

params.name: parentMD5
params.comment: the md5 string of the parent object

params.name: fileMD5
params.comment: the md5 string of this object

throws.comment: if missing or bad md5 values.

methods.name: get
methods.comment: Retrieves a filename mapping from this cache.

params.name: parentMD5
params.comment: the md5 string of the parent object

params.name: name
params.comment: the name of the requested object.

throws.comment: if missing or bad parent md5 values.

return.comment: the md5 string of the requested object, or null if not in cache.

name: FileCacheNameIndex
comment:
A best-effort cache of MD5 values of files, where the file is identified by its parent's
 MD5 combined with the file's path inside its parent's 'namespace'.

fields.javadoc:
An unlimited size, soft-reference, cache of file md5 values, keyed by a name specific
 to a parent file.
